that relate to trafficking is a challenge found by the Irish Human Rights Commission. The 
Commission has also noticed a lack in consistency and interpretation in application of the 
indicators of a trafficking victim. The Islamic Human Rights Commission faces a number 
of challenges, including a lack of any comprehensive laws on prevention, a lack of a single 
and unified definition on the issue, a lack of supportive measures to protect victims, a lack 
of training courses, the existence of discriminatory laws, a lack of monitoring and a lack of 
a comprehensive database to gather information. The Islamic Human Rights Commission 
itself lacks sufficient means to take effective action. The National Human Rights 
Commission of Nepal reported that challenges to its work include a lack of skilled human 
resources and coordination, a weak network of NGOs, lack of integration between policy 
and practice and a lack of a national database. 
